Given an array, find the smallest element.

Example:
arr = [4, 2, 9, 1, 6]
Output: 1

let arr = [4, 2, 9, 1, 6];

let smallest = arr[0];   // assume first element is smallest

for (let i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (arr[i] < smallest) {
        smallest = arr[i];
    }
}

console.log("Smallest element is:", smallest);

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
